  "text": "The common pumping scheme of holmium is shown in Fig. 3(a) . For direct pumping of singly-doped holmium, the absorption bands of interest lie at wavelengths of 1.15 μm ( 4 I 7 level) and 1.95 μm ( 5 I 7 level). Pumping of the 4 I 7 level can be addressed by 1.12 μm laser diodes [CITATION_1] or long wavelength operation of ytterbium fiber lasers [CITATION_2] . However, the low quantum efficiency of this pumping scheme limits its efficiency and power scaling potential. Alternatively, the 5 I 7 level can be accessed by thulium fiber or on-chip lasers, which can provide a high-power pump source at 1.95 μm.",
